other_name-1">A11Y=E2=80=94Accessibility=E2=80=99s Other Name</h2><p>A11Y i=
s the abbreviation=E2=80=94a numeronym, to be exact=E2=80=94for accessibili=
ty, where =E2=80=9C11=E2=80=9D represents the number of letters between the=
 letters A and Y. Often, people in the design field use the shorthand on <a=
 href=3D"https://www.interaction-design.org/literature/topics/social-media"=
 title=3D"What is Social Media in UX/UI Design?">social media</a> or in blo=
gs when they refer to accessibility-related topics and have a limited word =
or character count.&nbsp;</p><p>We can pronounce A11Y as =E2=80=9CA-one-one=
-Y,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CA-eleven-Y=E2=80=9D or even as =E2=80=9Cally,=E2=80=
=9D but it=E2=80=99s best just to say =E2=80=9Caccessibility.=E2=80=9D As w=
ith most abbreviations, A11Y is a form of jargon, so be sure to clarify its=
 meaning upfront with any audience that might not understand it, whether in=
 writing or verbally.&nbsp;</p><figure><img data-src=3D"https://public-imag=
es.interaction-design.org/tags/A11Y.png" alt=3D"" loading=3D"lazy" width=3D=
"2000" height=3D"1600"><figcaption><p>Remember, when designers create produ=
cts and services with accessibility in mind, they often design better produ=
cts for everyone. No matter the name, A11Y is key to inclusive design.  </p=
><p><small class=3D"copyright">=C2=A9 Interaction Design Foundation, CC BY-=
SA 4.0</small></p></figcaption></figure><h2 id=3D"accessibility_vs_usabilit=
y-2">Accessibility vs Usability</h2><figure><img data-src=3D"https://public=
-images.interaction-design.org/tags/td_accessibility_01.png" alt=3D"" loadi=
ng=3D"lazy" width=3D"1001" height=3D"553"></figure><p>Since they have simil=
arities, accessibility is sometimes confused with <a href=3D"https://www.in=
teraction-design.org/literature/topics/usability">usability</a>. Both overl=
ap and are vital parts of <a href=3D"https://www.interaction-design.org/lit=
erature/topics/ux-design">user experience (UX) design</a>, but there are al=
so key distinctions between them. <a href=3D"https://www.interaction-design=
.org/literature/topics/usability" title=3D"What is Usability?">Usability</a=
> is concerned with whether designs are effective, efficient and satisfying=
 to use.</p><p><!-- start video:1636 -->
