        <div id=3D"what-is-web-accessibility" class=3D"rteContent rteConten=
t--bodyLineHeight rteContent--imageFit">
        <p>Web Accessibility, as explained by Frank Spillers, is fundamenta=
lly about optimizing the user experience for everyone, ensuring that conten=
t is accessible, inclusive, and user-friendly, regardless of ability. It al=
igns closely with usability, focusing on simplifying layouts, optimizing co=
de, and making content more understandable and navigable, especially for sc=
reen-reader users. Accessibility goes beyond usability, emphasizing the nee=
d for content to be usable and accessible to all, promoting equality and in=
clusion on the web. Further insights on web accessibility can be gleaned fr=
om this video by Frank Spillers.</p><p><!-- start video:121 -->
