ntent rteContent--bodyLineHeight rteContent--imageFit">
        <p>An example of poor accessibility is a website lacking alt text f=
or images that are meant to convey meaning. This causes issues for visually=
 impaired users relying on screen readers. Poor accessibility is a crucial =
aspect of design failures and bad user experience, as illustrated in our ar=
ticles on <u><a href=3D"https://www.interaction-design.org/literature/artic=
le/bad-ux-examples">Bad UX Examples</a></u> and <u><a href=3D"https://www.i=
nteraction-design.org/literature/article/design-failures">Design Failures</=
a></u>. Explore more on the impact of inadequate accessibility at interacti=
on-design.org.</p><p><!-- start video:906 -->
