                What Is the Difference Between Accessibility and Inclusion?=
=20
            </div>
            <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden=3D"true" =
class=3D"svg-icon accordionItem__chevron">
    <use xlink:href=3D"#chevron-down"></use>
</svg>
        </div>
    </summary>
    <div class=3D"accordionItem__content js-accordionItem__content ">
        <div id=3D"what-is-the-difference-between-accessibility-and-inclusi=
on" class=3D"rteContent rteContent--bodyLineHeight rteContent--imageFit">
        <p>Accessibility is focused on making products and content usable f=
or everyone, regardless of disabilities, by removing barriers and optimizin=
g user experiences. It emphasizes adaptations and adjustments to accommodat=
e individual needs. On the other hand, inclusion refers to the proactive de=
sign of products, services, and environments that are welcoming and usable =
for a diverse range of people from the start. It=E2=80=99s about designing =
universally, considering all users' varied needs and preferences. For deepe=
r insights and understanding of inclusion, refer to <u><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.interaction-design.org/literature/topics/inclusive-design">this article =
on Inclusive Design</a></u>.</p>
    </div>
    </div>
</details>
